# <type>[optional scope]: <description>

# [optional body]

# [optional footer(s)]


# tips for commit
# type: fix, feat, perf, docs, refactor, style, chore, merge, test, build, ci, logs
# add ! for breaking change or BREAKING CHANGE: at the footer
# scope: should be specific parts of the code you touched like fixi_state or client
# body: start with a verb, imperative present tense. No "." at the end. No capitalizaiton
# think of following the sentence "this commit should/will"
# footer types: Fixes/Closes/Resolves, Relates-to/References/See-also, Co-authored-by, Reviewed-by, Signed-off-by

# to know more about conventionalcommits
# https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/

# example
#
# fix(INS-0000 algo)!: remove code that caused infinite loop
#
# Fix issue in setup screen with a polygon the shape of a lion, when pressing next - we get stuck.
#
# BREAKING CHANGE: by removing the infinite loop I had to change the api slightly
# instead of /loopi which is now removed, we should go to /loopahhh
#
# Co-authored-by: DonaldT
# Relates-to: INS-0002
# Resolves: INS-0000
